### 3. JavaScript — Show/Hide Logic

Each page's `setLoading()` function was updated to toggle `spinnerOverlay.classList.add/remove("active")`:

**[app.js](file:///c:/Users/Mayukh%20Jain/VS/NSOC/Medicsan_ai/static/js/app.js)** (index page):
```diff
-function setLoading(isLoading) {
+function setLoading(isLoading, showSpinner = false) {
   if (isLoading) {
     ...
+    if (showSpinner && spinnerOverlay) spinnerOverlay.classList.add("active");
   } else {
     ...
+    if (spinnerOverlay) spinnerOverlay.classList.remove("active");
   }
 }
```

The `showSpinner` parameter defaults to `false` so that non-AI calls (favorites, PDF, etc.) don't trigger the big spinner — only `fetchMedicine()` passes `true`.

**Inline JS** (compare, interaction, assistant): All three pages' `setLoading()` functions unconditionally toggle the spinner since every action on those pages is an AI call.

